Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @butternut squash{1} then halve lengthways
(no need to peel!) and scoop out the seeds. Chop it widthways into 2cm lengths,
then chop into 2cm cubes. Pop on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season
with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the
top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway
through cooking.

While the squash is roasting, trim off the root and the dark green leafy part
from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways. Roughly chop
the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a
#garlic press{}). Pick the @thyme{1%sprig} and @sage{1%sprig} leaves from their
stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Chop the @lemon{1/2} in half.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot,
add the mushrooms and leek and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir
in the garlic, thyme, sage and a pinch of @chilli flakes{1/2%tsp} and cook for
another minute. Pour in the @water{100%ml} and stir in the
@vegetable stock powder{1}. Stir in the @chopped kale{100%g} a handful at a time
and simmer until wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir the @crème fraîche{} and @wholegrain mustard{1%tbsp} into the veggies,
bring to the boil then remove from the heat. When the squash is done, remove
from the oven and stir into the veggies. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Transfer the mixture to an #ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle with the
@panko breadcrumbs{10%g}. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the topping
is golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> For really golden crumbs, mix a splash of oil through the crumbs before
> sprinkling.

Meanwhile, squeeze the lemon juice into a large #bowl{}, add the
@honey{7.5%ml} and stir together. Add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and
@hazelnuts{25} and toss to combine.

Serve the gratin with a good helping of salad alongside. Enjoy!